#
Now, the cement wall is a fancy, brick wall. The fairy lights are gone. [p]
The menu and the plastic plants are replaced by shelves of wine and posters of jazz singers.[p]
The last time he was in that damned café was graduation night, eight years ago. [p]
And he waited hours for Haruno Sakura to show up.[p]
But she never did, and he never found out why.[p]

[_tb_end_text]

